{"id":"279864407_Computing_Runs_on_a_General_Alphabet","abstract":"We describe a RAM algorithm computing all runs (=maximal repetitions) of a\ngiven string of length $n$ over a general ordered alphabet in\n$O(n\\log^{\\frac{2}3} n)$ time and linear space. Our algorithm outperforms all\nknown solutions working in $\\Theta(n\\log\\sigma)$ time provided $\\sigma =\nn^{\\Omega(1)}$, where $\\sigma$ is the number of distinct letters in the input\nstring. We conjecture that there exists a linear time RAM algorithm finding all\nruns.","authors":["Dmitry Kosolobov"],"meta":["July 2015Information Processing Letters 116(3)","DOI:10.1016/j.ipl.2015.11.016","SourcearXiv"],"references":["220897217_Lecture_Notes_in_Computer_Science","220770538_Lecture_Notes_in_Computer_Science","220658009_The_complexity_of_minimum_difference_cover","220570026_Detecting_leftmost_maximal_periodicities","47841538_Fast_Lightweight_Suffix_Array_Construction_and_Checking","2865732_Two_Simplified_Algorithms_for_Maintaining_Order_in_a_List","289573577_Online_Detection_of_Repetitions_with_Backtracking","285127301_A_general_technique_for_managing_strings_in_comparison-driven_data_structures","275588343_Faster_Lightweight_Lempel-Ziv_Parsing","269636452_Online_Repetition_Detection_With_Backtracking","265908817_Lempel-Ziv_Factorization_May_Be_Harder_Than_Computing_All_Runs","262891610_Quorums_from_difference_covers","248779657_Fast_algorithms_for_finding_nearest_common_ancestor","244434235_Linear_Time_Recognition_of_Squarefree_Strings","243763693_A_Theorem_in_Finite_Projective_Geometry_and_Some_Applications_to_Number_Theory","232743670_Time-Space_Trade-Offs_for_Longest_Common_Extensions","226698591_Fast_Lightweight_Suffix_Array_Construction_and_Checking","225035654_Fast_Algorithms_for_Finding_Nearest_Common_Ancestors","221313926_Theoretical_and_Practical_Improvements_on_the_RMQ-Problem_with_Applications_to_LCA_and_LCE","220780132_Dynamic_weighted_ancestors","220153709_Efficient_on-line_repetition_detection","